Document: CanvasLayer
Path: godot/classes/class_canvaslayer.rst
Summary: This section details the properties available for the CanvasLayer class in Godot Engine.

Properties:
- custom_viewport (Node): The viewport to which this CanvasLayer will be drawn. If null, the current scene's viewport is used.
- follow_viewport_enabled (bool): If true, the layer will follow the viewport's movement. Default: false.
- follow_viewport_scale (float): The scale factor applied when following the viewport. Default: 1.0.
- layer (int): The layer number. Layers with higher numbers are drawn on top of layers with lower numbers. Default: 1.
- offset (Vector2): The offset applied to the layer. Default: Vector2(0, 0).
- rotation (float): The rotation of the layer in radians. Default: 0.0.
- scale (Vector2): The scale of the layer. Default: Vector2(1, 1).
- transform (Transform2D): The transform of the layer. Default: Transform2D(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0).
- visible (bool): Whether the layer is visible. Default: true.
---CHUNK---
Document: CanvasLayer
Path: godot/classes/class_canvaslayer.rst
Summary: This section describes the methods and signals available for the CanvasLayer class in Godot Engine.

Method: get_canvas() → RID
Returns the RID of the canvas this CanvasLayer is drawn on.

Method: get_final_transform() → Transform2D
Returns the final transform of the CanvasLayer, taking into account its parent's transform and its own transform.

Method: hide() → void
Hides the CanvasLayer.

Method: show() → void
Shows the CanvasLayer.

Signal: visibility_changed()
Emitted when visibility of the layer is changed. See visible property.
---CHUNK---
Document: CanvasLayer
Path: godot/classes/class_canvaslayer.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the CanvasLayer class in Godot Engine.

Property: custom_viewport
Type: Node
Description: The custom Viewport node assigned to the CanvasLayer. If null, uses the default viewport instead.
Method: set_custom_viewport(value: Node)
Method: get_custom_viewport() → Node

Property: follow_viewport_enabled
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If enabled, the CanvasLayer maintains its position in world space. If disabled, the CanvasLayer stays in a fixed position on the screen. Together with follow_viewport_scale, this can be used for a pseudo-3D effect.
Method: set_follow_viewport(value: bool)
Method: is_following_viewport() → bool

Property: follow_viewport_scale
Type: float
Default: 1.0
Description: Scales the layer when using follow_viewport_enabled. Layers moving into the foreground should have increasing scales, while layers moving into the background should have decreasing scales.
Method: set_follow_viewport_scale(value: float)
Method: get_follow_viewport_scale() → float

Property: layer
Type: int
Default: 1
Description: Layer index for draw order. Lower values are drawn behind higher values.
Note: If multiple CanvasLayers have the same layer index, CanvasItem children of one CanvasLayer are drawn behind the CanvasItem children of the other CanvasLayer. Which CanvasLayer is drawn in front is non-deterministic.
Note: The layer index should be between RenderingServer.CANVAS_LAYER_MIN and RenderingServer.CANVAS_LAYER_MAX (inclusive). Any other value will wrap around.
Method: set_layer(value: int)
Method: get_layer() → int

Property: offset
Type: Vector2
Default: Vector2(0, 0)
Description: The layer's base offset.
Method: set_offset(value: Vector2)
Method: get_offset() → Vector2

Property: rotation
Type: float
Default: 0.0
Description: The layer's rotation in radians.
Method: set_rotation(value: float)
Method: get_rotation() → float

Property: scale
Type: Vector2
Default: Vector2(1, 1)
Description: The layer's scale.
Method: set_scale(value: Vector2)
Method: get_scale() → Vector2

Property: transform
Type: Transform2D
Default: Transform2D(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0)
Description: The layer's transform.
Method: set_transform(value: Transform2D)
Method: get_transform() → Transform2D

Property: visible
Type: bool
Default: true
Description: If false, any CanvasItem under this CanvasLayer will be hidden. Unlike CanvasItem.visible, visibility of a CanvasLayer isn't propagated to underlying layers.
Method: set_visible(value: bool)
Method: is_visible() → bool
---CHUNK---
Document: CanvasLayer
Path: godot/classes/class_canvaslayer.rst
Summary: Provides descriptions for the methods available on the CanvasLayer class.

Method: get_canvas() → RID
Returns the RID of the canvas used by this layer.

Method: get_final_transform() → Transform2D
Returns the transform from the CanvasLayer's coordinate system to the Viewport's coordinate system.

Method: hide() → void
Hides any CanvasItem under this CanvasLayer. This is equivalent to setting visible to false.

Method: show() → void
Shows any CanvasItem under this CanvasLayer. This is equivalent to setting visible to true.